subSubSection.paragraph:
Colouration (

Figs. 
3–4

) predominantly dark brown to black (labrum, clypeus, frons, pronotum, scutellum, most parts of elytra); elytra usually with two pairs of yellowish to pale brown patches (

Fig. 
3

); basal patches cross-strip-like, in very dark specimens inconspicuous, lacking (

Fig. 
4

) or reduced to one or two small spots at each elytron; ventral side brown to dark brown; maxillary palpi, femora, tibiae, and claws yellowish to pale brown; areas around the knee, and tarsomeres dark brown; antennae yellowish to pale brown, distally darkened.
